<p>In this project, we treat every pixel in an image as a biological cell. Then we train these cells to send signals to their neighbors so that, over time, the entire population will agree on what MNIST digit they are shaping. Every cell ‚Äúvotes‚Äù on the global shape by turning one of ten different colors, corresponding to the ten digits 0-9. Sometimes the truth prevails and sometimes they are collectively misguided. Sometimes conflicting signals cause different regions to be classified differently. I like <a href="https://twitter.com/hardmaru/status/1299152583328559105">@hardmaru‚Äôs example</a> of a 4 (üî¥) vs a 2 (üîµ). It‚Äôs similar to an election process. Even has ‚Äúswing states:‚Äù</p>

<div class="imgcap" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width:99.9%">
